qas.question: What town did Eisenhower retire to after his presidency?
What Pennsylvania county did Eisenhower grow up in?
Who did Eisenhower donate his farm to in 1967?
Who was the Republican presidential candidate in 1964?
What did Barry Goldwater call Eisenhower?

context: Eisenhower retired to the place where he and Mamie had spent much of their post-war time, a working farm adjacent to the battlefield at <a0_0>Gettysburg<a0_0/>, Pennsylvania, only 70 miles from his ancestral home in Elizabethville, <a1_0>Dauphin<a1_0/> County, Pennsylvania. In 1967 the Eisenhowers donated the farm to the <a2_0>National Park Service<a2_0/>. In retirement, the former president did not completely retreat from political life; he spoke at the 1964 Republican National Convention and appeared with <a3_0>Barry Goldwater<a3_0/> in a Republican campaign commercial from Gettysburg. However, his endorsement came somewhat reluctantly because Goldwater had attacked the former president as "a <a4_0>dime-store New Dealer<a4_0/>".
